ghout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Devonshire","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from the county of Devon, also known as Devonshire (see   Devon  ). Compare   Devonish  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Devon","meanings":["Mainly North American: of uncertain origin. It is found among Jews as well as gentiles. Among the latter it is generally from the name of the English county, either directly or as a transferred use of the surname, which derives from a British tribal name said to mean ‘worshippers of the god Dumnōnos’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret of Devonshire was born in 1330, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married Robert de Holway II about 1348, in Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1380, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1330–1380":"1330–1380","1328–1380":"1328–1380","1354–1395":"1354–1395","Abt 1354":"umbes 1354","1354":"1354","about 1348":"umbes 1348","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Holway, Somerset, England":"Holway, Somerset, England","Holway, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Holway, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Holway, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1330–1380":"1330–1380","1328–1380":"1328–1380","1354–1395":"1354–1395","Abt 1354":"noin 1354","1354":"1354","about 1348":"noin 1348","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1380":"1380","1328":"1328","Holway, Somerset, England":"Holway, Somerset, England","Holway, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Holway, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Holway, Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1330–1380":"1330–1380","1328–1380":"1328–1380","1354–1395":"1354–1395","Abt 1354":"environ 1354","1354":"1354","about 1348":"env